[normal]SPEAKER’S COMMITTEE ON THE ELECTORAL COMMISSION[bold]&#xa0;[bold]DRAFT AMENDMENTS[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Electoral Commission
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.(1) Schedule 1 to the Political Parties, Elections and Referendums Act 2000 (the Electoral Commission) is amended as follows.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](2) For paragraph 8(3) (committees) substitute–
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]“(3) A committee or sub-committee may include persons who are not Electoral Commissioners (“independent members”); and–
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]a committee or sub-committee may not include more than two independent members,
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]a person may not be appointed as an independent member if the person would be ineligible for appointment as an Electoral Commissioner by reason of section 3(4), and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]an independent member may do anything that another member can do (including chairing a committee or sub-committee).”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](3) In paragraph 15 (five-year plan)–
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](a) in sub-paragraph (1) after “as is mentioned in paragraph 14” insert “in respect of the first full financial year of each Parliament”,
[normal]              
[normal](b) after sub-paragraph (1) insert
[normal]&#xad;
[normal]–
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“(1A) A further plan must be submitted in respect of the third or fourth full financial year of each Parliament.” 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](4) In paragraph 16 (a
[normal]nnual examination of Commission by Comptroller and  Auditor General
[normal])–
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]in the heading omit “Annual”, and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]in sub-paragraph (1) after “in each year” insert “in respect of which a five-year plan is submitted”.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Local Government Boundary Commission for England
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.(1) Schedule 1 to the Local Democracy , Economic Development and Construction  Act 2009 (Local Government Boundary Commission for England) is amended as follows.
